Careers


Join the MOCON Team
MOCON Inc. is an international company headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota U.S.A. with offices worldwide.
With an increasingly global presence, we still maintain the family-like environment. We take pride in our culture that encourages innovation in our everyday work and in the dynamic markets we serve.
Our Vision
To increase the quality and safety of the environment and the products we consume
Our Mission
We provide unparalleled solutions by developing state-of-the-art test and measurement instruments and services on which our customers can depend
Our Values
• Integrity  • Innovation  • High-Quality   • Customer Focus   • Respect
At MOCON we live and breathe our Vision, Mission & Values as they are an integral part of our culture. Together we are...

Customer Oriented
Proactive and Progressive
Innovative
Results Oriented and Accountable
Solutions Seeking and Team Oriented
Empowering and Empowered
Transparent, Supportive, and Candid
Respectful





Minneapolis, USA


Director of Strategic MarketingRole Summary:
The Director of Global Strategic Marketing will lead the transition in her/his team from a product-centric Product Management Team to a more market-centric Strategic Marketing team. The Director plays a key role in top-line growth by strengthening the product pipeline by enhancing MOCON’s product development and by focusing on a highly professional “go-to-market” execution.




Technical Sales Specialist - Entry LevelRole Summary:
The Technical Sales Specialist role will support the Sales Team and Regional Customers by providing technical expertise, training and application knowledge.




Network & Systems AdministratorRole Summary:
The Network & Systems Administrator is part of a collaborative team of IT Professionals who work on highly visible, technically challenging projects and deliver comprehensive global solutions.Click to read more.




Customer Support SpecialistRole Summary:
Responsible for the delivery of customer satisfaction through efficient quoting, order handling, and order follow-up with customers via various communication channels.
							



Test Lab TechnicianRole Summary:
Perform MOCON testing procedures in a timely and accurate manner which identifies and solves product problems presented by film and package manufacturers and product users.
							



Lyons, Colorado USA


There are currently no open positions at our Lyons, CO office. Please check back soon!






We offer a competitive salary and comprehensive benefit package including medical and dental insurance, a flexible benefit package for medical and dependent care expenses; short-term and long-term disability, life and accidental death and dismemberment insurance, vacation, personal time off, holiday pay, 401(k) savings and retirement plan, stock options to qualified employees, tuition reimbursement and bonus program.







