PERMATRAN-W® Model 3/34





Home
InstrumentsPERMATRAN-W® Model 3/34
Automated to Save You Time
A stand alone fully automated water vapor transmission rate (WVTR) system. Ideal for those who need fast and accurate results. Easy to use for those new to permeation while offering the features needed for advanced users. Automatic maintenance of RH, temperature, pressure and flow. Complies with ASTM F-1249, JIS K7129 films and TAPPI T557. Ability to test in the same range as the PERMATRAN-W model 3/33 G.



Features
Specifications





Complies with ASTM F-1249. TAPPI T557. JIS K7129. ISO 15106-2
Compliance: CE/CSA/UL
TotalCal™
Stand alone with integrated computer
Intuitive touch screen interface
On-board data storage
Fully automated testing
Advanced testing with manual control
Faster time to results
Faster set up
Easy film placement
Horizontal pneumatically clamped test cells
Auto control of RH, pressure and flow
Auto temperature control
Auto sequential testing
Auto test save and printing
Package testing adapter (Optional)
High purge rate for packages
Fast, simple change from wet to dry testing
TruSeal® test cell
Ethernet and USB ready
Gas saver
Sensor over-range protection
Circuit board protection
Built-in calendar
Remote diagnosis
Individual Zero obtained on actual sample





Range






g/(m2 · day)
g/(100 in2 · day)
g/(pkg · day)


0.005 – 100
0.0003 – 6.45
0.000025 – 0.5




Repeatability: ±0.005 g/(m2 · d) or 2% of reading whichever is greater at 50 cm2
Resolution: 0.001 g/(m2 · d)
Temperature test range: 10Cto 40C ±0.2 C
Film test cells per module: 2 x 50 cm2 (pneumatic clamping cells)
Package testing: Optional package testing adapter cells available
Relative Humidity Range (RH):

Films - 0%. 5% – 90% and 100%
Test gas - Not controlled by instrument - Use Dry Nitrogen
Packages - Ambient


Test sample size:

Films - 4.0 in x 4.0 in (10.2 cm x 10.2 cm)
Packages - Up to 3 liters per package


Test database: Automatically saves up to 100 tests
Automatic sequential testing: With one set up, test 10 different RH and temperature parameters for the same film
User interface:

Touch screen with optional keyboard and mouse, remote access capable with optional PermNet® Lite.
Ethernet and USB ready












Contract testing services are also an option.
